# Project Rules

## Repository Purpose
This is a Rhino Python lab for procedural geometry experiments, reusable tools, and shared helper libraries. Scripts are written in Cursor and run inside Rhino's Python editor.

## Directory Layout
- `experiments/` — dated, self-contained studies (disposable)
- `tools/` — promoted scripts with UI wrappers (stable)
- `lib/` — shared helper modules imported by experiments and tools
- `docs/` — setup guide, conventions, experiment log
- `assets/` — sample geometry and screenshots
- `tests/smoke/` — lightweight sanity checks

## Key Conventions
- Experiments are named `YYYY-MM-topic/` and contain `script.py`, `notes.md`, and optionally `sample_inputs/`
- Tools contain `script.py` (logic), `ui.py` (Rhino UI), and `notes.md`
- All scripts add `lib/` to `sys.path` to access shared helpers
- See `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` for full runtime and API details
- See `docs/conventions.md` for naming and style rules

## When Generating Code
- Target IronPython 2.7 (no f-strings, no pathlib, no typing)
- Use `rhinoscriptsyntax` (as `rs`) for high-level ops, `Rhino.Geometry` (as `rg`) for low-level
- Include `scriptcontext` (as `sc`) when accessing the document or sticky dict
- Always add a `sys.path` insert for `lib/` at the top of experiment and tool scripts
- Prefer extracting reusable logic into `lib/` rather than duplicating across scripts

## Documentation
- **Always update `notes.md`** when adding, changing, or removing functionality in any experiment or tool
- Document new parameters, modes, and features with their ranges, defaults, and effects
- Keep the parameter tables and architecture sections current with the actual code
- Mark completed ideas as `[x]` in the Ideas to Explore list
- If a new experiment or tool is created, generate a `notes.md` alongside it
